== Description ==

This macro generates a cutlist for fabrication projects where parts are made from rectangular tubing, round bar, or angle iron. It reads all {{incode|Part::Box}} and {{incode|Part::Cylinder}} objects in the active document and outputs a CSV-formatted cutlist to the Report View.

For Box objects, the macro reports the two smaller dimensions as the profile size and the largest dimension as the length. For Cylinder objects, it reports the diameter and height. Objects must have a non-empty {{incode|Label2}} to be included in the cutlist; the macro uses Label2 to indicate the material profile (e.g., "roundbar", "squaretube").

== How To Use ==

# Model your fabrication design using {{incode|Part::Box}} primitives for square/rectangular stock and {{incode|Part::Cylinder}} primitives for round bar.
# Set the {{incode|Label}} of each part to indicate its role in the design (e.g., "top_rail", "leg").
# Set the {{incode|Label2}} of each part to indicate the profile type (e.g., "25x25_square", "16mm_round").
# Run the macro from {{MenuCommand|Macro → Macros... → FabricationCutlist}}.
# The CSV cutlist appears in the Report View ({{MenuCommand|View → Panels → Report View}}).

== Output Format ==

The output is a CSV with these columns:

|| Column || Description ||
| Timestamp | Can be discarded |
| Label | Part label (role in design) |
| Label2 | Profile type |
| Dim1 | For cylinders: diameter. For boxes: smaller profile dimension |
| Dim2 | For cylinders: blank. For boxes: larger profile dimension |
| Length | Cut length of the piece |

Objects without a Label2 value are skipped with a warning. Objects that are neither Box nor Cylinder are also skipped with a warning.

== Limitations ==

* Only {{incode|Part::Box}} and {{incode|Part::Cylinder}} objects are considered.
* Each object must have a non-empty {{incode|Label2}} field.
* Box dimensions are sorted so the two smallest values are treated as the profile and the largest as the length.
* Angle iron is not directly supported, but can be modeled as a Box with appropriate dimensions.

